      "id": 1,
      "text": "North Miami Beach was originally called Fulford‑by‑the‑Sea when Captain William H. founded it in 1926.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2,
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Miami_Beach%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The city adopted the name North Miami Beach in 1931 after the state legislature granted a new charter.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Miami_Beach%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The original street grid, laid out in 1917, still shows wide avenues like Fulford Boulevard, now Northeast 172nd Street.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
